h3. Problem Definition

From CONFDEV-25129 :
{panel}
See [this discussion. | https://extranet.atlassian.com/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=2216067400&focusedCommentId=2216068208#comment-2216068208]

We should remove the 'remember me' choice from the log in screen for the clustered version *only*. 'remember me' should be on by default.

Because this is a contentious decision we should supply a safety net. So there should be a system property that when set will restore the original behaviour or allowing the user to choose.
{panel}

For JIRA Data Center users, the user experience when a node fails depends on how long the node was down. If the user is moved to a different node, their login credentials are lost. Unless 'Remember me' is selected, users will have to log in again. This is a nuisance for customers that are using Data Center, as their users likely have not checked that box (as it isn't checked by default), and can precipitate multiple logins for their users.

h3. Suggested Solution

Have "remember me" checked as default for Data Center, as is the case with clustered Confluence servers. Create an override for customers that don't wish to have this configuration.

